                  <summary>Prescription for eye salve: the papyrus, written on both sides in the same hand, contains two medical prescriptions complete with titles and directions for use; originally published as accounts for medical supplies; the recto contains a recipe for an eye salve of the type commonly called achariston</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Written on both sides of the papyrus; the side published in ed. pr. as recto is written against the fibers, verso is written with the fibers</note>
